    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix m3ap_dump_MME_list function not iterating through MME entries correctly\n\n### Summary\nThe `m3ap_dump_MME_list` function was not properly iterating through MME entries to dump their information. Instead of traversing all MME entries in the red-black tree, it was attempting to find a specific entry using an empty search structure, which would always fail.\n\nThis caused the function to pass NULL pointers to `m3ap_dump_MME`, resulting in no MME information being displayed even when MME entries existed.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MME_management_procedures.c`: Modified `m3ap_dump_MME_list` function to properly iterate through all MME instances and entries using `STAILQ_FOREACH` and `RB_FOREACH` instead of trying to find a specific entry with `RB_FIND`.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Establish MME connections so that MME entries are populated in the red-black tree\n2. Call `m3ap_dump_MME_list()` function\n3. Observe that no MME information is printed despite existing entries\n4. The function would silently fail to dump any MME data due to incorrect iteration logic\n\nThe fix ensures that all MME entries are properly traversed and their information is displayed as expected.\n"
}